{
  "local_port": 55200,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I change gender in booked IRCTC e-tickets?",
  "response": "If you need to change the gender information on a booked IRCTC (Indian Railway Catering and Tourism Corporation) e-ticket, follow these steps:\n\n### 1. **Request a Gender Change via IRCTC Customer Care**\n   - Contact the IRCTC customer care team to request a gender change on your e-ticket.\n   - You can reach them via:\n     - **Phone**: Call the IRCTC customer care number at **139** (toll-free in India) or **+91-132-61392222** (for international callers).\n     - **Email**: Send an email to **care@irctc.co.in**.\n     - **Live Chat**: Use the live chat feature on the IRCTC website or mobile app.\n   - Provide the following details:\n     - PNR number\n     - Passenger name\n     - Correct gender to be updated\n     - Reason for the change (if required)\n\n### 2. **Visit the Reservation Counter**\n   - If contacting customer care is not feasible, visit the nearest railway station's reservation counter.\n   - Provide the PNR number and request the gender change in the passenger details.\n   - The railway staff will assist you in updating the gender information.\n\n### 3. **Carry Valid ID Proof**\n   - Ensure you carry a valid government-issued ID proof (e.g., Aadhaar, PAN, Passport) that matches the corrected gender information.\n   - This will be required if there is any verification during the journey.\n\n### Important Notes:\n- The gender change request must be made before the chart preparation (usually 4 hours before the departure time).\n- If the chart is already prepared, you may need to contact the Train Ticket Examiner (TTE) during the journey for assistance.\n- Gender changes are usually permitted only for genuine errors. IRCTC may reject requests if they suspect misuse.\n\nIf you encounter any issues, escalate the matter to the higher authorities at IRCTC or seek assistance at the railway station.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
